observations.managementAction:
1. Sent and reiterated correspondences to Landbank and DBP for further verification of the unrecognized deposits and unspecified withdrawals, which mostly constitute credit and debit memos directly added and deducted to the City's accounts. Copies of the letters sent to Landbank and DBP were also provided, for reference; 

2. Exerted efforts in the reconciliation of accounts, leading to a reduction in the unreconciled amount. As of 15 August 2024, the unreconciled amount had considerably decreased from P4.276 million to P1.187 million. A Detailed Summary of Unreconciled Accounts as of 2 August 2024 from the City Accountant's Office is also provided, for reference; 

3. Coordinated with Landbank to ease the monitoring of deposits and withdrawals through enrollment to the weAccess account, which allows the City to monitor the balances of the City's General Fund and SEF accounts and generate bank statements on a daily basis and when needed; 
4. Facilitated the issuance of Memorandum to concerned personnel to ease the liquidation of government funds given that one of the identified reasons for the unspecified withdrawals are the late transmittal of checks caused by the late turn-over of the Official Receipts required for the liquidation of disbursements (e.g., payment of utilities). A copy of the Memorandum is also furnished, for reference; and

5. Strengthened the regular reconciliation of the City's accounts to prevent accumulation of unreconciled items.

