observations.recommendation:
We recommended for the Municipal Mayor to:

1.Direct the Municipal Treasurer to exert more effort to expedite the collection of taxes due and collectible by sending demand letters to delinquent taxpayers giving priority to delinquent taxpayers having large balances, and;

2.Avail of the remedies provided for by law to enforce the strict and prompt collection of delinquent real property taxes.

We recommended Management to:

Immediately reconcile the cashbook balances with the subsidiary ledgers to ensure accuracy of the cash accounts; and

2. Prepare and timely submit bank reconciliation statements for all accounts maintained by the Municipality and ensure that balances reflected in the BRS are reconciled with the balances as shown in the trial balance;

We recommended to the Management the following courses of action:

Create or strengthen the LGU GFPS in accordance with MCW-IRR;

Establish and maintain a functional GAD Database which shall aid in gender analysis for the identification of gender issues and the cause/causes, to be addressed by the agency;

Ensure that identified PPAs address emerging gender-related issues and concerns.

We recommended the following courses of action:

Direct the HRMO to conduct a comprehensive review of the agency’s policy/practice of hiring with due regard to the actual needs of the office and the availability/non-availability of such kind of services among the regular employees and to impose strict supervision on attendance.  

Require the department heads/designated supervisors to prepare a detailed statement of duties and responsibilities as basis for work assignments and to ensure that actual accomplishments are relevant to the requirements of the office; 

Require job orders to prepare and submit accomplishment reports that are specific in terms of actual duties performed such that proper evaluation may be made on the necessity of hiring/re-hiring. Moreover, require job orders to ensure that the submitted accomplishment reports are duly signed by them and by their immediate supervisor;
Require job orders to attach a certified true copy of their logbooks to the DTR submitted for payroll. Moreover, require job orders to ensure that the DTRs submitted are duly signed by their immediate supervisor.

We recommended to the Management the following courses of action:

Refrain from using the 5% LDRRMF for expenditure items that are not directly related to disaster prevention and mitigation, preparedness, response, and rehabilitation and recovery;

Provide adequate funding for the regular operating expenses of the MDRRMO particularly for the repair and maintenance of motor vehicles;

We recommended to Management the following:

 Designate personnel to be in charge of the monitoring of the issuance of RIVs and preparation of the Daily Gas Issue Record/Log Book or its equivalent, and Fuel Consumption Report based on the format prescribed in the manual;

Direct the Municipal Engineering Office to submit the related program of works (POW) for the road maintenance activities and other projects requiring the use of various heavy equipment where a substantial quantity of the fuel was consumed, and submit the corresponding equipment utilization schedule/ report;

Stop the practice of allowing the use of government-procured fuel for privately-owned vehicles, advance payment of fuel which are yet to be consumed/ delivered and issuance of fuel quantities exceeding the fuel tank capacity of the heavy equipment, motor vehicle or motorcycle;

Consider the allocation of funds for the provision of motor vehicles and motorcycles to various offices/departments requiring the same to prevent the use of privately-owned vehicles for government transactions; and

We recommended the following courses of action:

1.	The Budget Officer shall ensure that all expenditures shall have a corresponding appropriation; 

