observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management:

Stop the practice of granting cash advance to disbursing or accountable officer for the purpose other than those provided in COA Circular 97-002. Also, activities or circumstances not covered by the said circular, like procurement of goods and services not petty in nature, shall undergo in the normal procurement process;

Avoid the recurrence of the above deficiencies, by proper planning so granting of cash advances will all be done without compromising the mandates of the law, rules and regulations;

Require the officer concerned to submit a written justification on why he should not be held liable for the noted violations of the procurement law which is the RA 9184 and its IRR, and COA Circular 97-002 regulating cash advances matter.

Ensure that an effective internal control environment be implemented through the following control policies and measures:  

a.  	Delegation of authority and supervision; 
b.   Segregation of functions for processing, reviewing, recording, custody and approval;
c.  	Access to resources and records; 
d. 	Completeness and integrity of transaction documents and reports;
e.  	Verification of transactions; and 
f.  	Reconciliation of records and data. [DBM Circular Letter No. 2008-8, the “National Guidelines  on Internal Control Systems (NGICS),” 23 October 2008, pp. 27-28].

